  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening the Health Sector preparedness and response for conflict-affected people against COVID-19 global pandemic</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Due to the prolonged crisis in Syria, the public health system is fragile and will require considerable support to reinforce its capacity to support a potential outbreak of COVID-19. Overall, only 57 public hospitals (50 percent2) are fully functioning in the country3 There is also a considerable shortage of trained staff and a high turnover rate, all of which reduce its capacity to manage cases and further puts the health workers on the frontline of response, at risks. Through this project, the PPEs for health care workers and medical equipment for case management of COVID-19 patients to be procured and delivered to MOH and health facilities. This include ultrasound scanners for pregnant patients of COVID-19 and thermometer for entry screening of health facilities.</narrative>
  </description>
